@abdonpijpelink ran into an error using STATS BY on an enrich field. Unless explicitly adding KEEP on the enrich policy's match field before the STATS...BY, the match field seems to be projected out.

Consider the following example using the Kibana sample web log data set.

```
PUT countries/_bulk
{ "index" : {}}
{ "geo.dest": "US", "country_name": "United States of America" }
{ "index" : {}}
{ "geo.dest": "IN", "country_name": "India" }
{ "index" : {}}
{ "geo.dest": "CN", "country_name": "China" }

PUT /_enrich/policy/countries
{
  "match": {
    "indices": "countries",
    "match_field": "geo.dest",
    "enrich_fields": ["country_name"]
  }
}

PUT /_enrich/policy/countries/_execute

# Not allowed
POST _query?format=txt
{
  "query": """
FROM kibana_sample_data_logs
| ENRICH countries
| STATS total_bytes = SUM(bytes) BY country_name
| SORT total_bytes DESC
| LIMIT 3
  """
}

# Allowed without STATS...BY
POST _query?format=txt
{
  "query": """
FROM kibana_sample_data_logs
| ENRICH countries
  """
}

# Allowed, if I use KEEP
POST _query?format=txt
{
  "query": """
FROM kibana_sample_data_logs
| KEEP bytes, geo.dest
| ENRICH countries
| STATS total_bytes = SUM(bytes) BY country_name
| SORT total_bytes DESC
| LIMIT 3
  """
}

# Pushing back ENRICH works too
POST _query?format=txt
{
  "query": """
FROM kibana_sample_data_logs
| STATS total_bytes = SUM(bytes) BY geo.dest
| SORT total_bytes DESC
| LIMIT 3
| ENRICH countries
  """
}
```

The error returned is
```
{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [
      {
        "type": "verification_exception",
        "reason": """Found 1 problem
line 3:3: Unknown column [geo.dest]"""
      }
    ],
    "type": "verification_exception",
    "reason": """Found 1 problem
line 3:3: Unknown column [geo.dest]"""
  },
  "status": 400
}
```

The ES|QL `COUNT_DISTINCT` function fails with an `illegal agg type: text` error when it's run on a `text` field. It's fine with `keyword` fields. Compare to for example `COUNT`, which runs fine on text fields:

```
PUT test/_doc/1
{
  "foo": "bar"
}

# This fails with illegal agg type: text:
POST /_query
{
  "query": """
    FROM test
    | STATS count = COUNT_DISTINCT(foo)
  """
}

# This works:
POST /_query
{
  "query": """
    FROM test
    | STATS count = COUNT_DISTINCT(foo.keyword)
  """
}

# COUNT is fine with text fields:
POST /_query
{
  "query": """
    FROM test
    | STATS count = COUNT(foo)
  """
}
```

Full error message:

```
{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [
      {
        "type": "esql_illegal_argument_exception",
        "reason": "illegal agg type: text"
      }
    ],
    "type": "esql_illegal_argument_exception",
    "reason": "illegal agg type: text"
  },
  "status": 500
}
```

